faster sintering

 Sintering is the process whereby individual resin particles fully coalesce with their neighbours so that the melting polymer is laid up against the mould wall. Lower viscosity leads to faster sintering time. Metallocenes with their narrower molecular weight distribution had a well defined melting point which allowed for a broader range of heating cycle times.
