I reject the proposition put forward in Mr Clements’ first report that once processing parameters have been optimized for ZN material it is unnecessary to repeat the exercise on any change of material. ;

(a)the exercise is dependent on the assumption that the relationship between ZN and borecene failure rates is a constant multiple. In fact failure rates declined or flattened out in 2005 for most materials (see paragraph 10.1.5 of Hassell 1 and the graphs at paragraph 2.9.1 of Hassell 3


		   The graphs also show that MFR 6 and  MFR 4 achieved considerably higher failure rates in years 1-5 than other grades. 

